What is Fault Tolerance? (IMPORTANT)

Fault tolerance is the ability of a system to continue working even when a component fails.

Failures can be:

Server crash

Disk failure

Data center outage

Network issues


#############


Simple Analogy (Use this if needed)
High Availability

Two engines, one running:

If engine fails â†’ switch engines

Small pause

Fault Tolerance

Two engines running together:

One fails â†’ other already running

No pause